Description:
Ship ahoy
Offered here 4 bedroom home with brilliant bay views. Imagine sitting at your dining table enjoying your meal and being able to also enjoy wonderful water views of Westernport Bay and French Island in Corinella. Situated just a short stroll to the 24 hour jetty, this home offers potential with so many extras. Open plan living, country style kitchen and a lovely front verandah perfect for those summer bay breezes and viewing those marvelous bay views. The property offers plenty of access for the boat or caravan with a garage at rear. Priced to sell, be quick for this property.

Description:
FORESHORE PICTURE PERFECT
This immaculate young home (approx.. 7 years) is designed to capture picturesque coastal and bay views. Featuring 3 generous size bedrooms all with BIRs, master having split-system air conditioner, water views and ensuite, open plan family and dining area ,cosy kitchen with all quality appliances, formal living also with split-system air conditioner, large family bathroom with full bath, good size laundry with door to private paved area with clothes line. Floating floors throughout except wet areas (bathroom/laundry/ensuite), ceiling fans in all rooms, double glazed windows, walls and roof fully insulated and attractive leadlight interior doors. Enjoy the tranquillity, water surround and distant coastal views when sitting on the back deck whilst watching the yachts and boats go by and the magical sunsets. The property is fully fenced with the backyard having established fruit trees. Double garage with back roller door for easy access to backyard. Situated on a large block approx.. 732sq.m. in a quiet court location in an exclusive estate of the popular Corinella well known for its great fishing. Only minutes to 24 hour boat ramp, 200 metres to shop, close to community centre, tennis courts, lawn bowls, v-line and school bus stops and great coastal walks. Small group of shops with local cafes, doctor and chemist and local wineries approx.. 8 mins and Phillip Island and major shopping centre approx.. 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway. We have obtained all information in this document from sources we believe to be reliable. However, we cannot guarantee its accuracy. Address: Lot 34 Portview Avenue/Buttonwood Way Grantville VIC 3984
Description:
Final Stage of Eastern Shores
Lot 34 Corner of Portview Avenue/Buttonwood Way, 504m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early 2018. The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
LUXURY WATERFRONT LIVING BREATHTAKING IN EVERY WAY
Enjoying a prime limited waterfront position, this impressive home is a haven of style, premium finishes and effortless liveability. Setting a new benchmark for luxury coastal living, 9 Mariners Court is located in a vibrant, high growth beach-side precinct of Corinella.
Simply superb from first impression to the last, this modern family home is designed for easy living and oozing character from care free indoor/outdoor entertaining. The floor plan boast’s exceptional functionality through a modern and well thought out design and looks out at the most stunning water views.
Thoughtfully designed the master bedroom offering the most stunning views with access on to the deck. Sleek kitchen with granite bench-tops, premium appliances and finishes flowing into the dinning and lounge open plan living with gas log fire and amazing views of French Island
Three stylish bathrooms with high end fixtures, Family bathroom with spa, Master ensuite offering therapeutic multifunction shower
The home offers a movie or games room, study, central heating / cooling throughout.
The outdoor area is an entertainer’s delight. It is the perfect place to sit and relax whilst entertaining family and friends, all overlooking the amazing water views.
Adjacent is a large foreshore reserve with room for the children to play & walking tracks.
Large remote controlled 2 car garage, The huge side access is ideal for caravan, boat or trailer also featuring Solar panels this amazing home has so much to offer.
SEPARATE ACCOMMODATION
Self – Contained 1 bedroom apartment with kitchenette and bathroom, BIR,s with independent access.
Please call Tamara or Daniel to arrange your private inspection.

1554 Bass Highway, Grantville - 10 Acres mixed Residential & Industrial
In a rapidly growing town of Grantville is this 10 acre site just adjacent to residential homes, with housing prices getting to expensive in town Grantville is becoming a main site for first home buyers.
Features: 10 Acres (4HA), mixed zone residential/industrial (council favouring rezoning to full residential), Mains water/sewage/storm water services available, Easy access highway frontage.
Site likes these go fast so be quick.

Description:
TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE!!
Feel the need to take in the clean country air but you do not want to live in isolation? This is for you!!
Chance to build your dream home on this rare vacant land. Situated within a short walk to shops and “the local pub”.
Whilst you and your family are enjoying a tree change lifestyle you are only an easy 10 minute drive to a favourite fishing spot on Westernport Bay, close to the highly regarded Lang Lang Golf Club and a stress free 28 km drive to Pakenham and all its amenities.
Developable area of 635m² ( approx.).
Whether you are starting out or downsizing this is an opportunity not to be missed.

Description:
I do love to be by the sea side.
Have you been waiting for the chance to buy a property in the coastal estate market? Well, here is your opportunity to own or invest in this 3 bedroom home by the bay. This immaculately presented brick veneer home is perfectly positioned.
Comprising
• A spacious lounge enjoys a wood heater and split system catering to your year round comfort.
• Kitchen with quality appliances and an abundance of storage and ample bench space.
• Formal lounge and dinning offering access to private rear deck ideal for entertaining.
• 3 robed bedrooms, including master with ensuite.
• A bright family bathroom.
• Practical laundry with toilet.
• Additional split system in formal dining/ lounge.
• Single car garage.
• Covered front deck.
• Shady side deck area with BBQ and water feature.
• Solar panels.
• Quality floor covering thru out.
• Established landscape gardens.
10 minutes from Grantville town centre and all the local amenities. This quality home has to be inspected to be fully appreciated. So if you are looking for a coastal change this low maintenance home is sure to delight.

Description:
Under Contract - Final Stage of Eastern Shores
Lot 17 Portview Avenue 750m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early 2018. The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
2.4 Ha(6 acres) with substantial 4 bedroom home & huge fully enclosed shed.
Homestead is set well back off quiet road with tree lined driveway making it very private. Home features a very large(approx. 14m x 9m) open plan living/kitchen/meals area with split system, dishwasher, gas and electric cooking, main bedroom with walk in robe and ensuite, 3 guest bedrooms with BIRs, lounge with double glass doors to living room, office with built in shelves & exterior door(this room is big...could be a 3rd living room), family bath room with bath, shower & separate toilet. Verandahs on 3 sides & double carport.
Property has sand dressage arena, lane way to 5 paddocks and 20m x 10m fully enclosed shed with 1 loose box, concrete floor 7 power.
Adjoins the foreshore and sandy beach. Close to town center.
A magnificent large home with horse facilities in great sea side location.

Description:
Perfect Location
Very well built and maintained 2 bedroom brick veneer unit, approx. 60 metres from the shops. This lovely unit has a full ensuite and walk in robe to the spacious master bedroom and generous sized 2nd bedroom with BIR. The lounge room and meals area are open plan and spacious in size. The functional kitchen has a good cupboard and bench space as well as a corner pantry electric hot plates and wall oven, double stainless sink and dishwasher. Front & rear external doors, have security doors. Reverse cycle air conditioning & heating , 2 door linen press and the laundry has a lovely bench and cupboard sink unit, plus a storage cupboard. Under roof outdoor area with a fully fenced backyard. The front yard is more like a court yard with established native trees giving you a nice private lawned area. This unit is in a perfect location with only a short walk to the shops, medical services, buses and school.

Description:
PANORAMIC BAY VIEWS - FORESHORE
The bay vista from this seaside home is a display of natural beauty that has to be seen. Situated opposite foreshore on a large block of approx.. 756 sq.m. is this split-level 3 bedroom home. Featuring upstairs -
- Open plan living/meals and kitchen area
- Dishwasher, stainless steel oven and gas hotplates
- Floating floor
- Split-system airconditioner
- 3 bedrooms all with BIRs
- Modern family bathroom with double shower
- Sliding door from living to wide balcony
- Magic water views from wherever you sit
- Downstairs -
- Rumpus room/4th bedroom
- Laundry combined with extra shower and toilet
- Storage room
The property also has a single garage, concrete driveway and area under home, at rear of property is gates for easy access to laneway at back and established gardens. Corinella is a popular destination for holidaymakers and keen fisherman with a 24 hour boat ramp and jetty and is very close to a safe sandy swimming beach and also offers scenic walking tracks to meander along. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx.. 25 mins and easy
commute to CBD with dual lane highway.
